[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA Jazzer-based fuzzing run detected a critical security issue in the codebase: an [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munguarded remote JNDI lookup during Log4j message processing. The fuzzer triggered [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical` exception when logging a crafted input, indicating [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat attacker-controlled JNDI URLs can be resolved at runtime. This behavior may [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallow remote code execution or data exfiltration depending on the JDK version.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue Type  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  A `com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical` was raised for a[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“Remote JNDI Lookup” vulnerability. This indicates that the application is [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mperforming JNDI lookups against attacker-supplied remote URLs.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability Details  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  JNDI lookups with unvalidated, remote targets can lead to:[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    • Remote code execution [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvia loading of malicious classes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    • Information leakage [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthrough JNDI responses[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Stack Trace Highlights  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. NamingContextLookup.lookupHook [0m[1;39m([0m[39msanitizer hook detecting the lookup[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. org.apache.logging.log4j.core.lookup.JndiLookup.lookup  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. org.apache.logging.log4j.core.lookup.Interpolator.lookup  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. org.apache.logging.log4j.core.lookup.StrSubstitutor.resolveVariable  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. org.apache.logging.log4j.core.pattern.MessagePatternConverter.format  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m. org.apache.logging.log4j.core.layout.PatternLayout.toSerializable  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m. AbstractOutputStreamAppender.append → LoggerConfig.log → AbstractLogger.warn  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Observations  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The issue is triggered during normal Log4j logging [0m[1;39m([0m[39min a `warn` call[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`SimpleLoggerFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m supplies input [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat is interpreted as a JNDI lookup string.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The lookup begins in Log4j’s `JndiLookup` and propagates through the pattern [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubstitution mechanisms.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         A fuzzing harness triggered a `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical` exception in Log4j’s    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         JndiLookup logic when performing a remote JNDI lookup with an attacker-controlled   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         URL. To mitigate this, the patch attempt changed the hardcoded `ENABLE_JNDI` flag   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         into a system-property-driven setting [1m([0m`log4j2.enableJndiLookup`[1m)[0m and added guards  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         in the `[1;35mlookup[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m` method to return null when JNDI is disabled. Corresponding     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         test code was added to verify both enabled and disabled scenarios. After applying   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         the patch, the core module failed to compile due to syntax errors in the updated    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `JndiLookupTest.java` [1m([0minvalid method declarations and stray statements outside of  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         any method[1m)[0m.                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Initial Issue                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - A jazzer-driven fuzzer run on Log4j’s `SimpleLoggerFuzzer` triggered:             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           `com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: Remote JNDI        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Lookup`                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Stack trace shows execution flowing into                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `org.apache.logging.log4j.core.lookup.JndiLookup.lookup`, then through Log4j’s      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         substitution mechanism.                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Remote JNDI lookups [1m([0m`ldap:[35m/[0m[35m/[0m…`, `rmi:[35m/[0m[35m/[0m…`[1m)[0m under attacker control can lead to    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         remote code execution or data exfiltration, depending on the JDK.                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Patch Attempt                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. In `JndiLookup.java`:                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Changed                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              `private static boolean ENABLE_JNDI = true;`                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              to                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              `private static boolean ENABLE_JNDI =                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mBoolean.parseBoolean[0m[1m([0m[1;35mSystem.getProperty[0m[1m([0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndiLookup"[0m, [32m"false"[0m[1m)[0m[1m)[0m;`      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Wrapped the public `[1;35mlookup[0m[1m([0mString key[1m)[0m` override in                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              `if [1m([0m!ENABLE_JNDI[1m)[0m return null;`                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. In `JndiLookupTest.java`:                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Switched from `@Before` to `@BeforeClass` to set the system property           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0m`log4j2.[33menableJndiLookup[0m=[35mtrue[0m`[1m)[0m and initialize a mock JNDI context via             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `MockContextFactory`.                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Added an `@AfterClass` to clear the system property.                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Added two test methods:                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • `[1;35mtestLookup[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` asserts a successful local JNDI lookup when enabled.          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • `[1;35mtestRemoteLookupDisabled[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` forces `log4j2.[33menableJndiLookup[0m=[35mfalse[0m`, calls a [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0mnon-existent[1m)[0m `[1;35mJndiLookup.setEnableJndi[0m[1m([0mfalse[1m)[0m`, then asserts that a remote URL    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         lookup returns null.                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Patch Result                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - During `mvn test-compile`, [1;36m10[0m syntax errors were reported in                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `JndiLookupTest.java`:                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • “invalid method declaration; return type required”                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • “[1m<[0m[1;95midentifier[0m[39m> expected”  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • “class, interface, or enum expected”  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The errors indicate that:  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Some method signatures [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlikely the new test methods[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are malformed or missing [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreturn types.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • There are stray statements [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `final StrLookup lookup = new [0m[1;35mJndiLookup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moutside any method or block.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • References to `[0m[1;35mJndiLookup.setEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` or `[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` do not match [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39many existing public API.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- JndiLookupTest.java  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Verify correct placement of braces and annotations. Ensure all methods have [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalid signatures and are enclosed in the class body.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Remove or relocate any test-related lines that ended up outside of methods.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Align test dependencies [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., correct `MockContextFactory` import and usage[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Add or expose public setter/getter methods on `JndiLookup` if tests intend to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcall `setEnableJndi` or `isEnableJndi`.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.example.SimpleLoggerFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1m([0mSimpleLoggerFuzzer.jav[1;92ma:42[0m[1m)[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         DEDUP_TOKEN: 03a39a742f79fa3d                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         == libFuzzer crashing input ==                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The initial issue is a Jazzer-detected `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical` indicating     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         that Log4j’s `JndiLookup` mechanism performs remote JNDI lookups, which can be      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         abused for remote code execution or data exfiltration when attacker-controlled URLs [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         are supplied. A patch was attempted by adding and modifying unit tests in           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `JndiLookupTest.java` to enable and disable JNDI lookups via system properties, and [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         to cover local and remote lookup behavior. However, after applying the patch, the   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         fuzzer still triggers the same `Remote JNDI Lookup` exception, showing that the     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         test changes did not prevent the underlying JNDI lookup hook from firing during     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         fuzzing.                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. Initial Issue                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - A Jazzer fuzzer run against Log4j’s lookup subsystem produced a                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: Remote JNDI Lookup`. [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The stack trace shows the vulnerability surfacing in                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `NamingContextLookup.lookupHook` → `JndiLookup.lookup`, propagating through         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `StrSubstitutor` → `PatternLayout` → logger appenders.                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The fuzzer harness [1m([0m`SimpleLoggerFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput`[1m)[0m eventually        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         exercises a code path where an attacker-controlled JNDI URL is resolved, triggering [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         the security sanitizer.                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. Important Observations                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The issue is flagged at the call to `JndiLookup.lookup`, indicating that       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         remote JNDI lookups are not prevented by default.                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The sanitizer hook [1m([0m`NamingContextLookup.kt:[1;36m61[0m`[1m)[0m is detecting a remote URL     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         even when tests are meant to disable JNDI lookups.                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. Patch Attempt                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - File modified:                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `core/src/test/java/org/apache/logging/log4j/core/lookup/JndiLookupTest.java`.      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Changes:                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Converted `@Before`[35m/[0m`@After` to `@BeforeClass`[35m/[0m`@AfterClass` to set up and   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         tear down a mock JNDI context once per test class.                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Added `[1;35mSystem.setProperty[0m[1m([0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndiLookup"[0m, [32m"true"[0m[1m)[0m` in setup and   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         cleared it in cleanup.                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Retained `[1;35mMockContextFactory.setAsInitial[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` and context binding of          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `logging/context-name` → `app-[1;36m1[0m`.                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Expanded `[1;35mtestLookup[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` to explicitly assert local and prefixed lookups and  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         null for non-existent names.                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Introduced `[1;35mtestRemoteLookupDisabled[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` which sets                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `log4j2.[33menableJndiLookup[0m=[35mfalse[0m`, calls `[1;35mJndiLookup.setEnableJndi[0m[1m([0mfalse[1m)[0m`, and       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         asserts that a lookup for `ldap:[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[95mattacker.example.com[0m` returns null.               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Imports were reorganized to include `javax.naming.Context`, `InitialContext`,  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `NamingException`, and relevant Log4j lookup classes.                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. Patch Result                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - After applying the test-only changes, the custom fuzzer continues to hit the   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         same JNDI lookup code path and triggers `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: Remote JNDI   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Lookup`.                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The stack trace remains unchanged, indicating that the patch has not altered   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         the production code paths that perform remote lookups under fuzzing.                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m. Areas for Further Investigation                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The implementation of `[1;35mJndiLookup.lookup[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m`: how the `enableJndiLookup`     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         property and any internal flags are read and enforced at runtime.                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The `NamingContextLookup.lookupHook` sanitizer logic and its interaction with  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         remote vs. local JNDI URLs.                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The initialization sequence of `StrSubstitutor` and `PatternLayout` to see     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         whether system properties are respected before any lookup hooks are registered.     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The static state within `JndiLookup` [1m([0me.g., any cached “enabled” flags[1m)[0m and    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         whether calls to `[1;35msetEnableJndi[0m[1m([0mfalse[1m)[0m` affect already-instantiated objects.        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The fuzzer harness [1m([0m`SimpleLoggerFuzzer`[1m)[0m to determine how it constructs       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         lookup strings and whether it bypasses the property-based guard.                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         This report provides a detailed account of the issue, the test-oriented patch, and  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         the fact that further work is needed in the production lookup code to prevent       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         remote JNDI resolution under fuzzing.                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The initial issue arises from a Jazzer-detected security finding in Apache Log4j’s  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         JndiLookup implementation: remote JNDI lookups using attacker-controlled URLs can   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         lead to RCE or data exfiltration. The user attempted to mitigate this by gating     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         JndiLookup on a new boolean property [1m([0m`log4j2.enableJndiLookup`[1m)[0m read via           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mPropertiesUtil.getBoolean[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m, false[1m)[0m`. After applying the patch, the core module  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         fails to compile with an error indicating that `PropertiesUtil` has no              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mgetBoolean[0m[1m([0mString, boolean[1m)[0m` method.                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. Initial Issue                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Exception thrown during fuzzing:                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              `com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: Remote JNDI     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Lookup`                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Stack trace location:                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • `NamingContextLookup.lookupHook` →                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `org.apache.logging.log4j.core.lookup.JndiLookup.lookup` → Log4j core               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         pattern/layout/appender code → user’s `SimpleLoggerFuzzer`.                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Security concern: remote JNDI lookups with attacker-controlled URLs may permit [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         remote code execution or information disclosure, depending on JDK version.          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. Important Observations                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The failure is raised by a Jazzer sanitizer hook in `NamingContextLookup.kt`,  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         not by application logic.                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The vulnerable code lives in                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `org.apache.logging.log4j.core.lookup.JndiLookup`.                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Fuzzer harness [1m([0m`SimpleLoggerFuzzer`[1m)[0m is merely invoking log4j logging         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         functionality and is not itself at fault.                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. Patch Attempt                                                                    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m              `import org.apache.logging.log4j.util.PropertiesUtil;`                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Introduced a constant for the system/property name:                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              `private static final String LOG4J_ENABLE_JNDI = [32m"log4j2.enableJndiLookup"[0m;`   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Changed the static flag initialization from `true` to reading the property:    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              `private static boolean ENABLE_JNDI =                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mPropertiesUtil.getBoolean[0m[1m([0mLOG4J_ENABLE_JNDI, false[1m)[0m;`                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.example.SimpleLoggerFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1m([0mSimpleLoggerFuzzer.jav[1;92ma:42[0m[1m)[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         DEDUP_TOKEN: 03a39a742f79fa3d                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         == libFuzzer crashing input ==                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The initial issue is a Jazzer-detected security finding in Apache Log4j Core: a     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         remote JNDI lookup that can lead to remote code execution or data exfiltration when [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         attacker-controlled URLs are resolved. The fuzzer trigger originates in             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `JndiLookup.lookup`, invoked during message formatting by the Log4j core.           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         A patch was attempted to disable JNDI lookups by default and drive enablement via a [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         system property [1m([0m`log4j2.enableJndiLookup`[1m)[0m. This involved importing                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `PropertiesUtil`, defining `LOG4J_ENABLE_JNDI`, and initializing the static         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `ENABLE_JNDI` flag using `[1;35mPropertiesUtil.getBooleanProperty[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m`.                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         After applying the patch, the build failed with a compilation error:                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         “non-static method [1;35mgetBooleanProperty[0m[1m([0mjava.lang.String,boolean[1m)[0m cannot be           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         referenced from a static context,”                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         indicating that `getBooleanProperty` is not a static method and thus cannot be      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         called in a static initializer.                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. Initial Issue                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            • A Jazzer FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical exception is thrown when                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `JndiLookup.lookup` is invoked with an attacker-controlled URL.                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            • The stack trace shows the call hierarchy: `NamingContextLookup.lookupHook` →   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `JndiLookup.lookup` → `Interpolator` → `StrSubstitutor` → logging appenders → user  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         fuzzer harness [1m([0m`SimpleLoggerFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput`[1m)[0m.                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            • The vulnerability arises from unconditional or enabled-by-default remote JNDI  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         resolution in the Log4j lookup plugin.                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. Important Observations                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            • JndiLookup uses a static boolean `ENABLE_JNDI = true` by default.              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            • There is no guard against remote JNDI URLs unless `ENABLE_JNDI` is toggled at  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         runtime.                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            • The fuzzer harness is merely the entry point; the core issue is in how         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `JndiLookup` is initialized and invoked.                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. Patch Attempt                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            • Added import: `org.apache.logging.log4j.util.PropertiesUtil`.                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            • Introduced a constant `LOG4J_ENABLE_JNDI = [32m"log4j2.enableJndiLookup"[0m`.         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            • Changed static flag initialization to:                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              private static boolean ENABLE_JNDI =                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mPropertiesUtil.getBooleanProperty[0m[1m([0mLOG4J_ENABLE_JNDI, false[1m)[0m;                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            • Intended effect: JNDI lookup disabled unless system property is explicitly set [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         to true.                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. Patch Result [1m([0mCompilation Log[1m)[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            • Build fails in `JndiLookup.java` at line [1;36m33[0m, column [1;36m56[0m.                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            • Error: “non-static method [1;35mgetBooleanProperty[0m[1m([0mjava.lang.String,boolean[1m)[0m cannot  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         be referenced from a static context.”                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            • Maven summary shows `log4j-core` module compilation failure; other modules     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         succeed.                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m. Areas for Further Investigation                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            • The PropertiesUtil API: determine which methods are static vs. instance and    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         how to retrieve boolean properties at initialization time.                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            • Static initialization in `JndiLookup`: consider alternatives for delayed or    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         instance-based property resolution.                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            • Other lookup plugins or core classes that rely on static configuration flags   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         and how they handle property access.                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            • Plugin loading and lifecycle in Log4j Core to understand when and how lookup   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         instances are constructed.                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            • Interaction between `PropertiesUtil`, `Configuration`, and system properties   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         to ensure consistent behavior across environments.                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Initial Issue Log                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m<[0m[1;95missue[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
